  {
    "type": "response.output_text.done",
    "sequence_number": 140,
    "item_id": "msg_85dd04ef0e824475b6f4337f7c1bba8c",
    "output_index": 0,
    "content_index": 0,
    "text": "That’s a big question! Since I don't know exactly what you're working on right now, \"what to do next\" could mean a lot of different things. \n\nTo give you the best advice, it helps to break it down. Here are a few suggestions depending on your situation:\n\n**1. If you're feeling overwhelmed or bored:**\n*   **Take a micro-break:** Stand up, stretch, drink a glass of water, or step outside for 5 minutes.\n*   **Brain dump:** Grab a piece of paper and write down everything on your mind. Pick the easiest 1 or 2 things to do first.\n\n**2. If you're working on a project or studying:**\n*   **Define the very next physical action:** Instead of thinking \"I need to finish my essay,\" think \"I need to open a Word document and write the title.\" Breaking things down makes them easier to start.\n*   **Use the Pomodoro technique:** Work on a single task for 25 minutes, then take a 5-minute break. \n\n**3. If you're looking for personal direction or goals:**\n*   **Do a quick life audit:** Rate your satisfaction right now in areas like Career, Health, Relationships, and Finances out of 10. Which one needs the most attention?\n*   **Try something new:** Pick a documentary to watch, a book to read, or a hobby to research that you normally wouldn't.\n\n**Tell me a bit more about your situation!** Are you stuck on a task? Trying to plan your day? Or feeling a little lost in general? If you share a bit more context, I can give you a much better recommendation.",
    "logprobs": []
  },
